Here’s a single DTS you can drop in as MCC_SHAKEDOWN.DTS that:

keeps your DBF bring-up / smoke sections

adds a “CALC builtins matrix” that tries to hit every function-like thing you currently show in HELP (ALLTRIM/ASC/AT/ATC/CHR/CTOD/DATE/DTOC/LEN/LEFT/LOWER/LTRIM/MAX/MIN/PAD*/PROPER/REPLICATE/RIGHT/RTRIM/SPACE/STR/STUFF/SUBSTR/TIME/TRANSFORM/TRIM/UPPER/VAL + your homegrown DATEADD/DATEDIFF/NOW/DATETIME/TODAY)

uses your rule: any expression with = >= <= starts with ( so CALC won’t think it’s CALCWRITE.

It also intentionally includes a few “canary” comparisons that you’ve seen return .F. (DATE()=TODAY(), MIN/MAX/VAL/STR/TRANSFORM returning .F., etc.)-that’s useful to surface “registered in HELP but not actually wired into the CALC evaluator”.

* ============================================================
* MCC_SHAKEDOWN.DTS - My Community College DBFs
* CALC Function/Operator Test Suite (full matrix)
*
* RULES / NOTES
* - Any CALC expression containing "=", ">=", "<=" MUST start with "("
*   or CALC will interpret it as CALCWRITE syntax.
*     GOOD:  CALC (UPPER("a") = "A")
*     BAD :  CALC UPPER("a") = "A"     && triggers CALCWRITE usage
*
* - BOOLEAN is best kept to field-only predicates (no function calls),
*   since BOOLEAN parsing differs from CALC expression parsing.
* ============================================================

SET ECHO ON
ECHO ===== DotTalk++ MCC SHAKE-DOWN START =====

COLOR DEFAULT
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
SCHEMAS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: LITERALS / ARITH / PRECEDENCE =====
CALC 1
CALC 1 + 2
CALC 10 - 3
CALC 6 * 7
CALC 8 / 2
CALC (1 + 2) * 3
CALC 1 + 2 * 3
CALC 7 / 2
CALC 7.0 / 2
CALC 0 - 5
CALC -5 + 2
CALC 1 + -2
CALC (0 - 2) * 3

* OPTIONAL canary (divide-by-zero behavior)
* CALC 1 / 0

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: COMPARISONS / BOOLEAN LOGIC (CALC PARSER) =====
CALC (1 = 1)
CALC (1 < 2)
CALC (2 > 1)
CALC (2 >= 2)
CALC (2 <= 2)
CALC (NOT (1 = 2))
CALC ((1 = 1) AND (2 = 2))
CALC ((1 = 1) OR (1 = 2))
CALC ((1 = 2) OR (2 = 2))

* precedence sanity
CALC (1 + 2 * 3 = 7)
CALC ((1 + 2) * 3 = 9)

* OPTIONAL: if "<>" is supported by CALC expr
* CALC (1 <> 2)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: CLOCK / DATE-TIME (NO DBF REQUIRED) =====
CALC DATE()
CALC TODAY()
CALC TIME()
CALC NOW()
CALC DATETIME()

* identity canaries (these currently come back .F. for you; keep as a regression signal)
CALC (DATE() = TODAY())
CALC (NOW() = DATETIME())

* date +/- days + compare
CALC DATE() + 2
CALC DATE() - 2
CALC ((DATE() + 2) > DATE())
CALC ((DATE() - 2) < DATE())

* CTOD parsing
CALC CTOD(2000-01-01)
CALC CTOD("2000/01/01")
CALC CTOD(20000101)

* CTOD comparisons + arithmetic
CALC (CTOD(2000-01-01) = 20000101)
CALC (CTOD("2000/01/01") = 20000101)
CALC (CTOD(20000101) = 20000101)
CALC CTOD(2000-01-01) + 1
CALC CTOD(2000-01-01) - 1
CALC ((CTOD(2000-01-01) + 1) = 20000102)
CALC ((CTOD(2000-01-01) - 1) = 19991231)

* DTOC round-trip canary (you currently see .F. on the compare; keep it)
CALC DTOC(CTOD(2000-01-01))
CALC (CTOD(DTOC(CTOD(2000-01-01))) = 20000101)

* OPTIONAL: DTOS if/when registered
* CALC DTOS(CTOD(2000-01-01))
* CALC (CTOD(DTOS(CTOD(2000-01-01))) = 20000101)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== BASIC COMMAND SANITY =====
HELP
AREA

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== OPENED DBFs (QUICK SANITY) =====
ECHO -- BUILDING
SELECT BUILDING
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- ROOMS
SELECT ROOMS
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- DEPT
SELECT DEPT
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- MAJORS
SELECT MAJORS
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- TERMS
SELECT TERMS
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- COURSES
SELECT COURSES
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- TEACHERS
SELECT TEACHERS
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- CLASSES
SELECT CLASSES
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- STUDENTS
SELECT STUDENTS
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- ENROLL
SELECT ENROLL
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- STUD_MAJ
SELECT STUD_MAJ
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

ECHO -- TASSIGN
SELECT TASSIGN
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
LIST 3
TUP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: FIELD READS / TYPE PATHS (STUDENTS) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LIST 1
TUP SID
TUP LNAME
TUP FNAME
TUP DOB
TUP ENROLL_D
TUP GPA
TUP EMAIL

CALC SID
CALC LNAME
CALC FNAME
CALC DOB
CALC ENROLL_D
CALC GPA
CALC EMAIL

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: NUMERIC OPS + NUMERIC BUILTINS =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LIST 1

ECHO -- numeric ops on fields (GPA)
CALC GPA + 1
CALC GPA - 1
CALC GPA * 2
CALC GPA / 2
CALC (GPA > 3)
CALC ((GPA >= 2) AND (GPA <= 4))

ECHO -- MIN/MAX (registered aggregate function that returning .F.  for you = canary)
CALC MIN(1, 2)
CALC MAX(1, 2)
CALC MIN(GPA, 4)
CALC MAX(GPA, 4)
CALC (MIN(1, 2) = 1)
CALC (MAX(1, 2) = 2)

ECHO -- VAL/STR/TRANSFORM (registered; currently returning .F. for you = canary)
CALC VAL("123.45")
CALC STR(123.45)
CALC STR(123.45, 10, 2)         * if width/decimals supported
CALC TRANSFORM(123.45)
CALC TRANSFORM(123.45, "999.99") * if picture/mask supported
CALC (VAL("123") = 123)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: DATE FIELDS + DATE ALGEBRA (STUDENTS) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LIST 1

CALC DOB
CALC ENROLL_D

* date +/- days (operator path)
CALC DOB + 1
CALC DOB - 1
CALC ((DOB + 1) > DOB)
CALC ((DOB - 1) < DOB)

* DATEADD / DATEDIFF (homegrown funcs you already have working)
CALC DATEADD(DOB, 30)
CALC DATEADD(DOB, -30)
CALC DATEADD(DATE(), 30)
CALC DATEADD(DATE(), -30)

CALC DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB)
CALC DATE() - DOB
CALC (DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB) = (DATE() - DOB))
CALC (DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB) > 0)
CALC (DATEDIFF(20260202, 20250114)
CALC (DATEDIFF("20260202","20250114")

* field-field date compare canary
CALC (ENROLL_D > DOB)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: STRING BUILTINS (LITERALS) =====
ECHO -- case conversion
CALC UPPER("aBc")
CALC LOWER("aBc")
CALC PROPER("joHN DOE")

CALC (UPPER("aBc") = "ABC")
CALC (LOWER("aBc") = "abc")
CALC (PROPER("joHN") = "John")

ECHO -- trim family
CALC ALLTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC LTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC RTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC TRIM("hi  ")                * TRIM is trailing trim in your HELP output

CALC (ALLTRIM("  hi  ") = "hi")
CALC (LTRIM("  hi  ") = "hi  ")
CALC (RTRIM("  hi  ") = "  hi")
CALC (TRIM("hi  ") = "hi")

ECHO -- length / slice / replace
CALC LEN("ABCDE")
CALC LEFT("ABCDE", 3)
CALC RIGHT("ABCDE", 2)
CALC SUBSTR("ABCDE", 2, 3)       * "BCD"
CALC STUFF("ABCDE", 2, 2, "ZZ")  * A ZZ DE -> "AZZDE" (depending on semantics)

CALC (LEN("ABCDE") = 5)
CALC (LEFT("ABCDE", 3) = "ABC")
CALC (RIGHT("ABCDE", 2) = "DE")
CALC (SUBSTR("ABCDE", 2, 3) = "BCD")

ECHO -- search
CALC AT("CD", "ABCDE")
CALC ATC("cd", "ABCDE")
CALC (AT("CD", "ABCDE") = 3)
CALC (ATC("cd", "ABCDE") = 3)

ECHO -- pad / space / replicate
CALC SPACE(3)
CALC REPLICATE("x", 5)
CALC PADL("7", 3, "0")
CALC PADR("7", 3, "0")
CALC PADC("7", 3, "0")

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: STRING BUILTINS (FIELDS) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LIST 1

CALC TUPLE UPPER(LNAME)
CALC TUPLE LOWER(LNAME)
CALC TUPLE PROPER(LNAME)
CALC TUPLE LEFT(LNAME, 3)
CALC TUPLE RIGHT(FNAME, 2)
CALC TUPLE ALLTRIM(EMAIL)
CALC TUPLE LEN(EMAIL)

* also try transforms that combine functions
CALC TUPLE (UPPER(LEFT(LNAME, 1)) + LOWER(SUBSTR(LNAME, 2)))
CALC TUPLE (ALLTRIM(FNAME) + " " + ALLTRIM(LNAME))

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: ASCII (ASC/CHR) =====
CALC ASC("A")
CALC CHR(65)
CALC (CHR(ASC("A")) = "A")

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== BOOLEAN / PREDICATE (FIELD-ONLY COVERAGE) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LIST 1
TUP GPA
BOOLEAN GPA > 3
BOOLEAN GPA < 3
BOOLEAN GPA >= 2 AND GPA <= 4
BOOLEAN LNAME = "Qui"
BOOLEAN LNAME = "Davis" OR LNAME = "Qui"
BOOLEAN GPA > 0 AND GPA < 10

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== LOCATE SMOKE (STUDENTS) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = DAVIS
TUP
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
TUP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALCWRITE: REVERSIBLE WRITE TEST (GPA += .01 then -= .01) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
TUP
LIST 1
TUP GPA
CALC GPA = GPA + 0.01
TUP GPA
CALC GPA = GPA - 0.01
TUP GPA


* ----------------- REPLACE SHAKEDOWN FOR STRING FUNCTION VALUES, DATE EXISTS BUT NOT IMPLEMENTED INTO REPLACE YET
TOP
REPLACE LNAME WITH LEFT(RIGHT(TRIM("   Washington "),5),2)
TUP
REPLACE DOB WITH ENROLL_D
TUP
* should be .f. until implemented
REPLACE DOB WITH DATE() - 1
TUP

MIN GPA
MAX GPA
AVG GPA
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== COLOR SANITY =====
COLOR GREEN
COLOR AMBER
COLOR DEFAULT

ECHO ===== CLEAN SHUTDOWN =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
ECHO ===== DotTalk++ MCC SHAKE-DOWN END =====
* QUIT

* Two quick takeaways from your run output (so this script won’t fight you)

* Comparisons inside CALC must start with ( - the script enforces that everywhere.

* Your results show a consistent pattern: some things listed as “implemented yes” in HELP still return .F. when 
* called from CALC (MIN/MAX/VAL/STR/TRANSFORM, plus DATE/TODAY equality). This suite keeps those as canaries so you 
* can see exactly when the CALC evaluator wiring gets fixed.

* If you want, paste the output of just the MIN/MAX/VAL/STR/TRANSFORM block after you run this; I can tell you * 
* whether it looks like “function not registered in CALC”, “type mismatch”, or “string-vs-number compare semantics”.